  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Edge<NodeType extends Node<NodeType,? extends Vector,?>>
    The edge object connects two nodes of the same type.
    Graph<NodeType extends Node<NodeType,? extends Vector,IdentifierType>,EdgeType extends Edge<NodeType>,IdentifierType>
    The graph contains nodes connected by edges of a certain type.
    Node<NodeType extends Node<NodeType,VectorType,IdentifierType>,VectorType extends Vector,IdentifierType>
    The node is the elementary object contained in graphs.
